  "chapter": {
    "number": 4,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Father’s Instruction"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen, my sons, to a father’s instruction;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "pay attention and gain understanding.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I give you sound teaching;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not abandon my directive.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When I was a son to my father,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "tender and the only child of my mother,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "he taught me and said,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Let your heart lay hold of my words;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "keep my commands and you will live.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Get wisdom, get understanding;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not forget my words or turn from them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not forsake wisdom, and she will preserve you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "love her, and she will guard you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Wisdom is supreme; so acquire wisdom.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "And whatever you may acquire,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4200
          },
          {
            "text": "gain understanding.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prize her, and she will exalt you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "if you embrace her, she will honor you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "She will set a garland of grace on your head;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "she will present you with a crown of beauty.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen, my son, and receive my words,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the years of your life will be many.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will guide you in the way of wisdom;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will lead you on straight paths.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When you walk, your steps will not be impeded;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when you run, you will not stumble.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hold on to instruction; do not let go.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Guard it, for it is your life.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not set foot on the path of the wicked",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or walk in the way of evildoers.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Avoid it; do not travel on it.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Turn from it and pass on by.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For they cannot sleep",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "unless they do evil;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they are deprived of slumber",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "until they make someone fall.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For they eat the bread of wickedness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and drink the wine of violence.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The path of the righteous is like the first gleam of dawn,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "shining brighter and brighter until midday.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But the way of the wicked is like the darkest gloom;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they do not know what makes them stumble.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My son, pay attention to my words;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "incline your ear to my sayings.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not lose sight of them;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "keep them within your heart.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For they are life to those who find them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and health to the whole body.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Guard your heart with all diligence,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for from it flow springs of life.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Put away deception from your mouth;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "keep your lips from perverse speech.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let your eyes look forward;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "fix your gaze straight ahead.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make a level path for your feet,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4201
          },
          {
            "text": "and all your ways will be sure.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not swerve to the right or to the left;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "turn your feet away from evil.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 4200,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or And whatever else you acquire",
